==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polysynthesis
<hw>Pol`y*syn"the*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>synthesis</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of combining many separate elements into a
whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>The formation of a word by the
combination of several simple words, as in the aboriginal languages of
America; agglutination.</def> <rj><au>Latham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polysynthetic</ent>⟦br⟧
